mosais.distribution

Class Quadtree<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • mosais.distribution.Quadtree<E>

  • public class Quadtree<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    A tree data structure where every inner node has exactly four children. Used to model two dimensional areas, recursively breaking the area down in quadrants. Data elements can only be stored at the leaf nodes. Whenever the node is divided, all data points stored at that node must be distributed to the child nodes.
    Author:
    Andrew Trismen
